  "features": [
    {
      "name": "Spellcasting",
      "html description": "<p>An event in your past, or in the life of a parent or ancestor, left an indelible mark on you, infusing you with arcane magic. This font of magic, whatever its origin, fuels your spells.</p>\n<h5>Cantrips</h5>\n<p>At 1st level, you know four cantrips of your choice from the sorcerer spell list.</p>\n<h5>Spell Slots</h5>\n<p>The Sorcerer table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your sorcerer spells of 1st level and higher. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a long rest.</p>\n<h5>Spells Known of 1st Level and Higher</h5>\n<p>You know two 1st-level spells of your choice from the sorcerer spell list.</p>\n<h5>Spellcasting Ability</h5>\n<p>Charisma is your spellcasting ability for your sorcerer spells.</p>\n<p><strong>Spell save DC</strong> = 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier</p>\n<p><strong>Spell attack modifier</strong> = your proficiency bonus + your Charisma modifier</p>\n<h5>Spellcasting Focus</h5>\n<p>You can use an arcane focus as a spellcasting focus for your sorcerer spells.</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Sorcerous Origin",
      "html description": "<p>Choose a sorcerous origin, which grants you features at 1st level and again at 6th, 14th, and 18th level.</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Font of Magic",
      "html description": "<p>At 2nd level, you gain sorcery points that you can use to create a variety of magical effects.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Sorcery Points.</strong> You gain sorcery points as shown in the class table and regain all spent points when you finish a long rest.</li>\n  <li><strong>Flexible Casting.</strong> You can create spell slots from sorcery points or convert spell slots into sorcery points (see “Creating Spell Slots”).</li>\n</ul>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Metamagic",
      "html description": "<p>At 3rd level, you gain two Metamagic options of your choice. You gain another at 10th and 17th level. You can use only one Metamagic option on a spell when you cast it, unless otherwise noted.</p>\n<p>This page lists many options, including Careful Spell, Distant Spell, Empowered Spell, Extended Spell, Heightened Spell, Quickened Spell, Seeking Spell (and UA variant), Subtle Spell, and Transmuted Spell.</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Ability Score Improvement",
      "html description": "<p>At 4th level, and again at 8th, 12th, 16th, and 19th level, you can increase ability scores as normal.</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Sorcerous Versatility (Optional)",
      "html description": "<p>Whenever you gain an Ability Score Improvement, you can optionally swap certain sorcerer choices (as listed on the page).</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Magical Guidance (Optional)",
      "html description": "<p>At 5th level, you can spend 1 sorcery point to reroll a failed ability check (per the optional feature on the page).</p>"
    },
    {
      "name": "Sorcerous Restoration",
      "html description": "<p>At 20th level, you regain a small number of sorcery points when you finish a short rest (per the class feature).</p>"
    }
  ]
}